@startuml
title Statistics Service - Diagrama de Componentes + Seguridad

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

package "API Management" {
    [API Gateway\n(APIM)] as APIM
}

package "Statistics Service\nPuerto: 5627" {

    [Statistics Controller\nREST Endpoints] as Controller
    [Swagger / OpenAPI] as Swagger
    [JWT Filter\nValida token JWT] as JwtFilter

    [Statistics UseCase\nLógica de negocio\n- Promedios\n- Totales\n- Rankings\n- Reconocimientos] as UseCase

    [Statistics Repository\nSpring Data MongoDB] as Repository

    [Tournament Client\nREST Client (Feign)\n+ Internal API Key] as TournamentClient
}

database "MongoDB\ntechcup_stats" as Mongo {
    [PlayerMatchStat]
    [TournamentRecognition]
}

component "Tournament Service\nPuerto: 8080" as Tournament
component "Competition Service" as Competition
component "Identity Service\nPuerto: 5620" as Identity

cloud "RabbitMQ" as Rabbit
queue "match.finished.queue" as MatchQueue

' === FLUJO JWT (Seguridad) ===
Identity --> APIM : 1. Emite JWT (/auth/login)
APIM --> Controller : 2. HTTPS Request + JWT
Controller --> JwtFilter : 3. Intercepta y valida
JwtFilter --> Identity : 4. GET /token/validate
JwtFilter --> Controller : 5. OK (sigue flujo) / 401

' === FLUJO HTTP ===
Swagger .. Controller : Documentación OpenAPI
Controller --> UseCase
UseCase --> Repository
UseCase --> TournamentClient

Repository --> Mongo : Spring Data
TournamentClient --> Tournament : REST + API Key
note right of TournamentClient
  GET /tournaments/active
  GET /tournaments/{id}
  POST /tournaments/{id}/recognitions
end note

' === FLUJO ASINCRONO (RabbitMQ) ===
Competition --> Rabbit : Publica MatchFinishedEvent
Rabbit --> MatchQueue
MatchQueue --> UseCase : Consume evento

@enduml
